I don&#39;t know if you are using Panache [with Hibernate Reactive][1] or [with Hibernate ORM][2], but, at the moment, if you want to use Panache, [you have to use a projection][2]:
```java
@RegisterForReflection
public class EntityRootIdView {
   public final Long rootId;

   public EntityRootIdView(Long rootId){ 
        this.rootId = rootId;
   }
}

// Panache with Hibernate ORM
List&lt;EntityRootIdView&gt; rootIds = Entity
    .find(&quot;SELECT DISTINCT t.rootId from Entity t&quot;)
    .project(EntityRootIdView.class)
    .list()

// Panache with Hibernate Reactive
Uni&lt;List&lt;EntityRootIdView&gt;&gt; rootIds = Entity
    .find(&quot;SELECT DISTINCT t.rootId from Entity t&quot;)
    .project(EntityRootIdView.class)
    .list()
```
Note that [this requires at least Quarkus 2.12.0.Final][3]

Alternatively, you can use the Hibernate Reactive session:
```java
Uni&lt;List&lt;Long&gt;&gt; rootIds = Panache.getSession()
    .chain(session -&gt; session
        .createQuery(&quot;SELECT DISTINCT t.rootId from Entity t&quot;, Long.class)
        .getResultList() )
    );
```

Or, if you are using Hibernate ORM, the entity manager:
```java
List&lt;Long&gt; rootIds = Panache.getEntityManager()
    .createQuery( &quot;SELECT DISTINCT t.rootId from Entity t&quot;, Long.class )
    .getResultList();
```

Funny enough, [I&#39;ve just created an issue to make this easier](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/28844).


  [1]: https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-reactive-panache
  [2]: https://quarkus.io/guides/hibernate-orm-panache#query-projection
  [3]: https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/26284

