As stated in the comments, you can gain access to the numerical value of the instance of `Number` using [the methods that this class][1] offers.

The method name checkEven implies that the parameter will be treated as an Integer, so you can use `intValue`. You can of course also check the `doubleValue` if that fits your needs more.

Of course this will only work for subclasses of `Number` that can be represented by an `int` or `double` respectively.


    static &lt;T extends Number&gt; boolean checkEven(T x){
        int numValue = x.intValue();
        return numValue % 2 == 0;
    }

You can also use intValue to implement that &quot;square the number&quot; method you mentioned in the comments.

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/lang/Number.html#doubleValue--

