There&#39;s a [breaking change in Docker Desktop 4.13 on macOS](https://docs.docker.com/desktop/release-notes/#docker-desktop-4130):

&gt; By default Docker will not create the /var/run/docker.sock symlink on the host and use the docker-desktop CLI context instead.

Spring Boot is [going to be updated to cope with this change](https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-boot/issues/32897). In the meantime, you should be able to create the symlink manually. Alternatively, you could configure Spring Boot to use `$HOME/.docker/run/docker.sock`:

```groovy
tasks.named(&quot;bootBuildImage&quot;) {
    docker {
        host = &quot;$HOME/.docker/run/docker.sock&quot;
    }
}
```

